Package org.cesecore.certificates.endentity

Class EndEntityInformation

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.cesecore.certificates.endentity.EndEntityInformation
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable
    public class EndEntityInformation
extends Object
implements Serializable
    Holds admin data collected from UserData in the database. Strings are stored in Base64 encoded format to be safe for storing in database, xml etc.
    Version:
    $Id: EndEntityInformation.java 34163 2020-01-02 15:00:17Z samuellb $

      • EndEntityInformation

        public EndEntityInformation​(String username,
                            String dn,
                            int caid,
                            String subjectaltname,
                            String email,
                            int status,
                            EndEntityType type,
                            int endentityprofileid,
                            int certificateprofileid,
                            Date timecreated,
                            Date timemodified,
                            int tokentype,
                            int hardtokenissuerid,
                            ExtendedInformation extendedinfo)
        Creates new EndEntityInformation. All fields are almost required in this constructor. Password must be set manually though. This is so you should be sure what you do with the password.
        Parameters:
        username - the unique username.
        dn - the DN the subject is given in his certificate.
        caid - CA id of the CA that the user is registered with
        subjectaltname - the Subject Alternative Name to be used.
        email - the email of the subject (may be null).
        status - Status of user, from EndEntityConstants.STATUS_NEW etc
        type - Type of user, from EndEntityTypes.ENDUSER etc, can be "or:ed" together, i.e. EndEntityTypes#ENDUSER | EndEntityTypes.SENDNOTIFICATION
        endentityprofileid - the id number of the end entity profile bound to this user.
        certificateprofileid - the id number of the certificate profile that should be generated for the user.
        timecreated - DOCUMENT ME!
        timemodified - DOCUMENT ME!
        tokentype - the type of token, from EndEntityConstants.TOKEN_USERGEN etc
        hardtokenissuerid - if token should be hard, the id of the hard token issuer, else 0.
        extendedinfo - info

      • EndEntityInformation

        public EndEntityInformation​(String username,
                            String dn,
                            int caid,
                            String subjectaltname,
                            String email,
                            EndEntityType type,
                            int endentityprofileid,
                            int certificateprofileid,
                            int tokentype,
                            int hardtokenissuerid,
                            ExtendedInformation extendedinfo)
        Creates new EndEntityInformation. This constructor should only be used from UserDataSource implementations. Status and dates aren't used in these cases.
        Parameters:
        username - the unique username.
        dn - the DN the subject is given in his certificate.
        caid - the id of the CA that should be used to issue the users certificate
        subjectaltname - the Subject Alternative Name to be used.
        email - the email of the subject (may be null).
        type - one of EndEntityTypes.USER_ENDUSER || ...
        endentityprofileid - the id number of the end entity profile bound to this user.
        certificateprofileid - the id number of the certificate profile that should be generated for the user.
        tokentype - the type of token, from EndEntityConstants.TOKEN_USERGEN etc
        hardtokenissuerid - if token should be hard, the id of the hard token issuer, else 0.
        extendedinfo - info

      • getDN

        public String getDN()
        User DN as stored in the database. If the registered DN has unused DN fields the empty ones are kept, i.e. CN=Tomas,OU=,OU=PrimeKey,C=SE. See ECA-1841 for an explanation of this. Use method getCertificateDN() to get the DN stripped from empty fields.
        Returns:
        String with DN, might contain empty fields, use getCertificateDN to get without empty fields
        See Also:
        getCertificateDN()

      • getCertificateDN

        public String getCertificateDN()
        Returns:
        the DN to be used when creating a certificate (without empty fields). If the registered DN has unused DN fields the empty ones are kept, i.e. CN=Tomas,OU=,OU=PrimeKey,C=SE. See ECA-1841 for an explanation of this. Use method getCertificateDN() to get the DN stripped from empty fields, getDN() returns DN with empty fields.
